This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring Thursday, November 27, 2014, as a National Day of Thanksgiving. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of reflecting on the blessings and freedoms enjoyed in America, expressing gratitude for the opportunities and sacrifices that have contributed to the nation's prosperity. It also highlights the historical significance of Thanksgiving, referencing the Pilgrims' journey for liberty and the Native tribe's support, as well as the tradition of coming together in times of war and peace. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate Thanksgiving with loved ones, show compassion towards others, and strengthen the ties that unite the diverse country.